  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "BzBzjx8b9A5w/WZNzW79M9qIRkA=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Argument\n\nGSOC (Graffiti Single Owner Chunks) is a many-to-one notification primitive on Swarm. A signer key is mined offline so that its SOC address falls in the reader's neighborhood; that signer is then shared with all writers. Writers create SOC updates, and the chunks sync via ordinary neighborhood replication \u2014 no Trojan mining per message.\n\n## Key properties\n\n- **Direction:** many-to-one (multiple writers \u2192 one reader)\n- **Encryption:** symmetric (shared signer key)\n- **Latency:** **milliseconds** (no per-message mining)\n- **Offline delivery:** yes \u2014 SOC persists in the neighborhood\n- **Setup cost:** one-time signer mining (~10\u201330s per peer)\n- **Receiver node:** full node only\n- **Stamp type:** must be mutable\n\n## API\n\n```typescript\nconst signer = bee.gsocMine(targetOverlay, identifier, proximity)\nawait bee.gsocSend(batchId, signer, identifier, data)\nconst sub = bee.gsocSubscribe(address, identifier, { onMessage, onError, onClose })\n```\n\n## Role in Connect\n\nGSOC is the low-latency rail for presence, doc-update pings, and collaboration signals \u2014 everything where the 2\u201310s PSS latency is unacceptable.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z"
    }
  },
